  "instructions": [
    "1. Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "2. In a bowl, mix together broken crisp bread, Tunisian harissa, toasted sesame seeds, diced charred red pepper, chopped parsley (if using), salt, and black pepper.",
    "3. Stir until well combined.",
    "4. Spoon the mixture onto a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.",
    "5. Bake for 10-12 minutes or until crispy and golden brown.",
    "6. Remove from oven and let cool for a few minutes.",
    "7. Serve warm or at room temperature."
